<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="agreement-n">agreement <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'ɡriːmənt/    美 /ə'ɡriːmənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>同意；(意见) 一致</strong></h4>
<p>反  disagreement： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s easier for two parties to <strong>reach agreement</strong> than for three. 
两方达成一致比三方达成一致要容易。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We are <strong>in agreement</strong> about the price.
关于价格我们意见一致。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>协定；协议：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sign an agreement 
签订协议</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>arrive at</strong> / <strong>come to</strong> / <strong>reach an agreement</strong> ( <strong>with</strong>)
(与…)达成协议</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>hold to / keep an agreement
遵守协议</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They had <strong>an agreement</strong> never to talk about work at home<strong> to</strong>
他们约定在家中绝不谈工作。</p></div></div>